ted with star-forming clouds and galaxies, then the\nglobal correlation for all scales has a near unity slope and an intercept\nconsistent with the (proto-)stellar accretion timescale, Mcs/Macc. Therefore,\nan additional critical test of our hypothesis is that the Macc-Mdisk\ncorrelation for Class II stars should also be observed between Macc and Mcs for\nClass 0/I sources with similar slope and intercept.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Aug 2018 09:56:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-24"}
